<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB43BD0FF78FCFDFE32FB24" blockId="485.[136,778,547,2070]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FF78FCFDFE08FC8C" bold="true" box="[189,461,819,845]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FDFDFCFDFD70FC8C" box="[568,693,819,845]" captionStart="FIGURE 322" captionStartId="486.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1344,211,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-20@486.[200,1387,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="486" captionText="FIGURE 322. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, D, 0.05 mm; C, E–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591949/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 322A</figureCitation>
) stout, ventrally curved; bodylength 1.01 mm. Prosome 808 μm long: dorsal cephalic shield expanded ventrolaterally, with small, paired, dorsally curved horn-likeprocesses (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FF55FC75FECEFC14" box="[144,267,955,981]" captionStart="FIGURE 322" captionStartId="486.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1344,211,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-20@486.[200,1387,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="486" captionText="FIGURE 322. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, D, 0.05 mm; C, E–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591949/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 322D</figureCitation>
) posterolaterally. Freeurosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FD52FC75FCC4FC14" box="[663,769,955,981]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="34.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[226,1362,199,1872]" captionTargetId="figure-19@34.[215,1373,188,1873]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 19. Notodelphys tenera Thorell, 1859, female. A, habitus, right; B, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, mandible; F, maxillule; G, maxilla; H, maxilliped; I, leg 5. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm; D–I, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591189/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 19B</figureCitation>
) 5-segmented. Caudalramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FE10FC13FD8CFC36" box="[469,585,989,1015]" captionStart="FIGURE 322" captionStartId="486.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1344,211,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-20@486.[200,1387,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="486" captionText="FIGURE 322. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, D, 0.05 mm; C, E–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591949/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 322C</figureCitation>
) about 3.2 times longer than wide (89×28 μm) and about twice as long as anal somite, with almost parallel lateral margins and rounded distal margin, ornamented with many scattered setules: armedwith 6 setae (outer lateral, dorsal, and 4 distal) outer lateral and dorsal setae positioned in same plane at 60% length of ramus; all caudal setae small, less than half width of ramus at base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB43BD0FF78FB20FDFBF99A" blockId="485.[136,778,547,2070]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FEE9FB23FE5EFAC6" box="[300,411,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 322" captionStartId="486.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1344,211,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-20@486.[200,1387,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="486" captionText="FIGURE 322. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, D, 0.05 mm; C, E–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591949/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 322E</figureCitation>
) large, 95×53 μm, proximal third with parallel lateral margins, distal two-thirds tapering towards blunt apex. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FE29FAFFFD9EFA8A" box="[492,603,1329,1355]" captionStart="FIGURE 322" captionStartId="486.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1344,211,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-20@486.[200,1387,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="486" captionText="FIGURE 322. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, D, 0.05 mm; C, E–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591949/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 322F</figureCitation>
) stout, strongly tapering, 9-segmented, but articulation between seventh and eighth segments incomplete; armature formula 2, 13, 5, 2+aesthetasc, 2, 3, 2, 2, and 7; all setae naked. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FF55FA77FEC7FA15" box="[144,258,1465,1492]" captionStart="FIGURE 322" captionStartId="486.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1344,211,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-20@486.[200,1387,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="486" captionText="FIGURE 322. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, D, 0.05 mm; C, E–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591949/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 322G</figureCitation>
) stout, 3-segmented, comprisingunarmed coxa and basis and unsegmented endopod; endopod about 2.5 times longer than wide (42×17 μm) and about 0.8 times as long as basis: armedwith 1 middle and 2 distalsetae plus terminal claw, half as long as endopod.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB43BD0FF78F9ADFBAAFECA" blockId="485.[136,778,547,2070]" lastBlockId="485.[810,1452,173,744]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FEEEF9ADFE61F9BF" box="[299,420,1635,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 322" captionStartId="486.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1344,211,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-20@486.[200,1387,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="486" captionText="FIGURE 322. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, D, 0.05 mm; C, E–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591949/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 322H</figureCitation>
) simple, with narrow setulose posterior margin. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FE12F94BFD80F961" box="[471,581,1669,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 322" captionStartId="486.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1344,211,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-20@486.[200,1387,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="486" captionText="FIGURE 322. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, D, 0.05 mm; C, E–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591949/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 322I</figureCitation>
) with broadened coxal gnathobase bearing 5 teeth and 1 seta; basis with 1 seta: exopod 2-segmented; first segment armed with 2 equal, large setae; secondsegment with 2 equal, distal setae and 1 small outer seta (about half as long as larger setae): endopod with 1 and 5 setaeon first and second segments, respectively; all setae short, subequal in length. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FECDF8BAFEB2F84F" box="[264,375,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 322" captionStartId="486.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1344,211,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-20@486.[200,1387,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="486" captionText="FIGURE 322. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, D, 0.05 mm; C, E–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591949/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 322J</figureCitation>
) armedwith 9 setaeon arthrite, 2 unequal setae on epipodite, 1 on basis, 4 on exopod, and 3 on endopod; coxal endite absent. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FD4EF876FCC7F813" box="[651,770,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 323" captionStartId="487.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1337,213,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@487.[205,1383,183,1868]" captionTargetPageId="487" captionText="FIGURE 323. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 3; F, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591951/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 323A</figureCitation>
) 4-segmented; syncoxa bearing 4, 2, and 2 setae on first to third endites, respectively; basis with smooth claw plus 1 seta; endopod small, lacking setaon first segment, with 3 setae on second segment. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FB19FF01FA8AFF28" box="[1244,1359,207,233]" captionStart="FIGURE 323" captionStartId="487.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1337,213,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@487.[205,1383,183,1868]" captionTargetPageId="487" captionText="FIGURE 323. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 3; F, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591951/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 323B</figureCitation>
) lobate, armedwith 6 subequal setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB43BD0FC9AFEDDFBCBFD26" blockId="485.[810,1452,173,744]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
Legs 1–3 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FC20FEDDFB8EFEEC" box="[997,1099,275,301]" captionStart="FIGURE 323" captionStartId="487.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1337,213,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@487.[205,1383,183,1868]" captionTargetPageId="487" captionText="FIGURE 323. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 3; F, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591951/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 323</figureCitation>
C-E) with 3-segmented rami. Leg 4 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FC4CFEFBFBC6FE8E" box="[905,1027,309,335]" captionStart="FIGURE 323" captionStartId="487.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1337,213,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@487.[205,1383,183,1868]" captionTargetPageId="487" captionText="FIGURE 323. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 3; F, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591951/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 323F</figureCitation>
) with 3-segmented exopod and 2- segmented endopod; second endopodal segment of leg 4 elongate, about 4.2 times longer than wide (54×13 μm), 3.5 times longer than first endopodal segment. Inner coxal seta absent on all swimming legs. Inner distal spine of basis of leg 1 small, 12 μm long. Second exopodal segment of leg 1 bearing outer seta (instead of spine). All setae on swimming legs naked, except feebly pinnate (or spinulose) setae on third exopodal segment of leg 3. Leg 4 asymmetical: outer setae on exopod of left leg 4 slender (as on leg 3), but setae on right leg 4 broad and spiniform (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FBE3FD65FB5BFD04" box="[1062,1182,683,709]" captionStart="FIGURE 323" captionStartId="487.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[208,1337,213,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@487.[205,1383,183,1868]" captionTargetPageId="487" captionText="FIGURE 323. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 3; F, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591951/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 323F</figureCitation>
). Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB43BD0FC9AFC10FB6DFB9C" blockId="485.[810,1452,989,1628]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
Leg 5 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB43BD0FC6BFC13FBE4FC36" box="[942,1057,989,1015]" captionStart="FIGURE 322" captionStartId="486.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1344,211,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-20@486.[200,1387,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="486" captionText="FIGURE 322. Doroixys obesa sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, D, 0.05 mm; C, E–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591949/files/figure.png" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Fig. 322B</figureCitation>
) represented by 2 tapering, pointed posteroventral processes on surface of somite; outer process smaller; inner exopodal process larger, armed with 1 small seta on outer margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB43BD0FC9AFBABFBE5FBBE" blockId="485.[810,1452,989,1628]" box="[863,1056,1125,1151]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FC9AFBABFC66FBBE" bold="true" box="[863,931,1125,1151]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EEB43BD0FC9AFB49FC01F99D" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB43BD0FC9AFB49FC01F99D" blockId="485.[810,1452,989,1628]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FC9AFB49FC09FB60" bold="true" box="[863,972,1159,1185]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Remarks</emphasis>
. This is the first species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB43BD0FAE1FB46FA4FFB60" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[1316,1418,1160,1185]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FAE1FB46FA4FFB60" box="[1316,1418,1160,1185]" italics="true" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be characterised by the possession of a 3-segmented antenna, comprising coxa, basis, and an unsegmented endopod, although additional new species sharing the same kind of 3-segmented antenna are described below. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB43BD0FCEFFAFCFC12FA8A" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[810,983,1329,1355]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FCEFFAFCFC12FA8A" box="[810,983,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">Doroixys obesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FC1AFAFFFBFDFA8A" bold="true" box="[991,1080,1329,1355]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB43BD0FC1AFAFFFBFDFA8A" box="[991,1080,1329,1355]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is unique within the genus in the absence of a seta on the first endopodal segment of the maxilla. Other unusual features include the endopod of the mandible is armed with 6 equal, short setae (1 on first and 5 on second segment, respectively) rather than setae of dissimilar lengths, and the maxillule bears 2 setae on the epipodite rather than the typical single seta. These features are sufficient to distinguish the new species from its congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
